title: Wall Street Breakfast June 14: Biggest Fed Rate Hike Since 1994 Now Overwhelmingly Expected
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: Biggest Fed rate hike since 1994 now overwhelmingly expected. Stock futures rebound, but traders remain wary as S&P 500 drops into bear market. Morgan Stanley's James Gorman sees 50% chance of U.S. recession. Elon Musk said set to address Twitter employees for first time this week. U.S. urging Russian fertilizer deals to help ease food costs - Bloomberg. Catch today’s WSB article here.
